div.p:
"Governor Tony Evers directed the Wisconsin Department of Health Services (DHS) Secretary, Andrea Palm, to extend the Safer at Home order from April 24, 2020 to 8:00 a.m. Tuesday, May 26, 2020, or until a superseding order is issued.”
The bulletin also noted that “public and private K-12 schools will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.” Please stay posted to the school website for more information about COVID-19 and how we can better communicate with one another and support one another through this difficult time.
